self.__next_f.push([1,".p.woff2\",\"font\",{\"crossOrigin\":\"\",\"type\":\"font/woff2\"}]\n:HL[\"/_next/static/css/3aa57f3c452e9377.css\",\"style\"]\nb:T4fb,\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\u003ch2\u003e\n\t\tInterruptible Single Timeline Enter/Exit\n\t\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tThis demo is an \u003cem\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eincredibly\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/em\u003e useful pattern for interruptible UI interactions with different enter and exit animations. It uses a single timeline with an \u003ccode\u003e.addPause()\u003c/code\u003e in the middle to separate the enter and exit animations. If the enter animation is playing and the user doubletaps quickly to close it, the entrance animation reverses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e Once the menu is fully open, tapping again plays forward into a completely different exit animation where the panels fall with random rotation. \u003ccode\u003eeaseReverse\u003c/code\u003e makes the reversal feel responsive by switching from \u003ccode\u003eback.out\u003c/code\u003e on enter to \u003ccode\u003epower3.in\u003c/code\u003e on reverse, so the menu gets out of the way quickly when someone changes their mind.\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tThis demo is covered in the following YouTube video\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003ciframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" id=\"ips_uid_8999_7\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wfzy0pvKiic?si=8UOL8Gzt6lC3-JBV\u0026amp;start=972\" style=\"aspect-ratio: 16/9\" title=\"YouTube video player\" width=\"100%\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\nc:T446,\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\u003ch2\u003e\n\t\t\u003ccode\u003eclear()\u003c/code\u003e and rebuild for different entrance and exits\n\t\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tThis animation pattern allows for different enter and exit animations. It reuses a single timeline and calls \u003ccode\u003e.clear()\u003c/code\u003e before rebuilding it with either the entrance or exit animation. The entrance uses \u003ccode\u003efromTo\u003c/code\u003e tweens so every open starts from a known state, in this case, panels slide in, items stagger, the hamburger morphs to an X. The exit uses \u003ccode\u003eto\u003c/code\u003e tweens so that the animation picks up from wherever things currently are, panels drop off-screen with random rotation while the icon reverts to bars.\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tT"])

