self.__next_f.push([1,"18:T497,\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\u003ch2\u003e\n\t\ttoggleActions\n\t\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\u003ccode\u003etoggleActions\u003c/code\u003e lets you control what your animation does at four key moments. \n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003col\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eonEnter\u003c/strong\u003e – when you scroll into the trigger zone (start trigger)\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eonLeave\u003c/strong\u003e – when scrolling out of the trigger zone (end trigger)\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eonEnterBack\u003c/strong\u003e – when scrolling back into the trigger area in the opposite direction\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eonLeaveBack\u003c/strong\u003e – when scrolling back out of the trigger area in the opposite direction\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tTo control your animation at these points you provide four instructions in a string like:\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\u003ccode\u003etoggleActions: \"play pause resume reset\"\u003c/code\u003e\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003ch3\u003e\n\t\tIn this example:\n\t\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eplay\u003c/strong\u003e – plays the animation when entering\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003epause\u003c/strong\u003e – pauses it when leaving\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003eresume\u003c/strong\u003e – continues it when entering again backwards\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003cstrong\u003ereset\u003c/strong\u003e – rewinds it to the beginning when scrolling back past the start trigger\n\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n19:T686,\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\u003ch2\u003e\n\t\tScrub\n\t\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\tScrub links the progress of the animation directly to the scrollbar so it acts like a scrubber. You can apply smoothing so that it takes a little time for the playhead to catch up with the scrollbar's position.\u003cbr\u003e\n\t\t \n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\u003cpre class=\"ipsCode prettyprint lang-javascript prettyprinted\" id=\"ips_uid_8839_12\" style=\"\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e gsap\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003eto\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"str\"\u003e'.flair'\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e\n  rotation\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lit\"\u003e360\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e\n  scrollTrigger\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pun\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pln\"\u003e\n "])

